-- Argentina Extends Time for Some Exporters to Repatriate Revenue
-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 2012-06-15T11:21:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-15/argentina-extends-time-for-some-exporters-to-repatriate-revenue.html
Argentina is extending the number of
days some companies have to bring back export revenue to the
country, according to the  official gazette .  The resolution lists 29 companies that are given from 60 to
180 days to repatriate foreign currency.  YPF SA (YPFD) , included in the
list, has as long as 90 days.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in Buenos Aires at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  